ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: While this course may seem like a whirlwind of topics in clinical science, this course nicely encapsulates them and emphasizes their relevance to clinicians and researchers alike.
This course is a good (and necessary) course for learning how to handle ethical dilemmas in clinical work.
This is a great class to provide practical knowledge in areas of psychotherapy which are not typically discussed in other classess

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: This course allowed me to understand the field at a variety of levels and consider how each of these levels (cultural, ethical, etc.) can be best integrated into my own research and clinical practice.
It helped deepen my knowledge of the profession of clinical psychology by highlighting ethical dilemmas and how to handle them.
This course provided a lot of practical knowledge for future clinical work
